{"timestamp": "2026-05-22 12:42:37,073", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-22T12:42:37.073476\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Implement clearing mechanics for Tetris line clears and Bejeweled match-3 clears, including chain reactions and bonus scoring.\", \"result\": \"```python\\nimport random\\nfrom typing import List, Tuple, Optional\\n\\nfrom task0 import Grid, GemCell, Color\\n\\n\\nclass ClearingManager:\\n    def __init__(self, grid: Grid):\\n        self.grid = grid\\n        self.score = 0\\n\\n    def clear_lines(self) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Clears complete lines and returns the number of lines cleared.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        lines_cleared = 0\\n        rows_to_clear = []\\n        for y in range(self.grid.height):\\n            if all(self.grid.get_cell(x, y) is not None for x in range(self.gri...\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"failed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n1. Line removal is brittle: removing rows one by one and shifting can misalign when multiple lines clear. It’s safer to rebuild each column by filtering out cleared rows and padding at the top.\\n2. Scoring is very simplistic: it only uses `cleared_count * 10` and `lines_cleared^2 * 100`. It’s better to use standard Tetris line scores (100/300/500/800) and apply a chain/combo multiplier for both match‐3 and line clears.\\n3. Chain reactions are only applied to match clears, not to line clears. It’s more intuitive to treat any clear (lines or matches) in the same chain step, with a single loop iteration per chain level.\\n4. `find_matches` can report overlapping runs multiple times; although deduplicated, we can optimize by scanning runs fully and then skipping ahead.\\n5. No bonus multiplier per chain level; adding a simple linear chain multiplier (e.g., ×1.0, ×1.5, ×2.0, …) rewards deeper chains.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\nimport random\\nfrom typing import List, Tuple, Optional\\n\\nfrom task0 import Grid, GemCell, Color\\n\\n# Standard Tetris line clear scoring\\nTETRIS_SCORES = {\\n    1: 100,\\n    2: 300,\\n    3: 500,\\n    4: 800,\\n}\\n\\nclass ClearingManager:\\n    def __init__(self, grid: Grid):\\n        self.grid = grid\\n        self.score = 0\\n\\n    def clear_lines(self) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Detects and removes all full rows, returns number of lines cleared.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        full_rows = [y for y in range(self.grid.height)\\n                     if all(self.grid.get_cell(x, y) is not None for x in range(self.grid.width))]\\n        if not full_rows:\\n            return 0\\n\\n        # Rebuild each column by filtering out cleared rows\\n        for x in range(self.grid.width):\\n            column_cells = [self.grid.get_cell(x, y) for y in range(self.grid.height)\\n                             if y not in full_rows]\\n            # Pad top with None\\n            new_col = [None] * len(full_rows) + column_cells\\n            for y, cell in enumerate(new_col):\\n                self.grid.set_cell(x, y, cell)\\n        return len(full_rows)\\n\\n    def find_matches(self) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Finds all match-3+ runs and returns unique gem coordinates.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        matches = set()\\n\\n        # Horizontal runs\\n        for y in range(self.grid.height):\\n            x = 0\\n            while x < self.grid.width - 2:\\n                cell = self.grid.get_cell(x, y)\\n                if cell is None:\\n                    x += 1\\n                    continue\\n                run_color = cell.color\\n                run_length = 1\\n                while x + run_length < self.grid.width and \\\\\\n                      self.grid.get_cell(x + run_length, y) and \\\\\\n                      self.grid.get_cell(x + run_length, y).color == run_color:\\n                    run_length += 1\\n                if run_length >= 3:\\n                    for rx in range(x, x + run_length):\\n                        matches.add((rx, y))\\n                x += run_length\\n        # Vertical runs\\n        for x in range(self.grid.width):\\n            y = 0\\n            while y < self.grid.height - 2:\\n                cell = self.grid.get_cell(x, y)\\n                if cell is None:\\n                    y += 1\\n                    continue\\n                run_color = cell.color\\n                run_length = 1\\n                while y + run_length < self.grid.height and \\\\\\n                      self.grid.get_cell(x, y + run_length) and \\\\\\n                      self.grid.get_cell(x, y + run_length).color == run_color:\\n                    run_length += 1\\n                if run_length >= 3:\\n                    for ry in range(y, y + run_length):\\n                        matches.add((x, ry))\\n                y += run_length\\n        return list(matches)\\n\\n    def clear_matches(self) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Clears all matched gems, drops floating gems, returns count cleared.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        matches = self.find_matches()\\n        if not matches:\\n            return 0\\n        for x, y in matches:\\n            self.grid.set_cell(x, y, None)\\n        self.drop_floating_gems()\\n        return len(matches)\\n\\n    def drop_floating_gems(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Gravity: drop gems down into empty spaces.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for x in range(self.grid.width):\\n            stack = [self.grid.get_cell(x, y) for y in range(self.grid.height)\\n                     if self.grid.get_cell(x, y) is not None]\\n            # pad with None at top\\n            new_col = [None] * (self.grid.height - len(stack)) + stack\\n            for y, cell in enumerate(new_col):\\n                self.grid.set_cell(x, y, cell)\\n\\n    def resolve_chains(self) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Repeatedly clears lines and matches until stable.\\n        Applies chain multipliers and returns total score gained.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        total_gain = 0\\n        chain_level = 0\\n\\n        while True:\\n            chain_level += 1\\n            multiplier = 1.0 + 0.5 * (chain_level - 1)\\n\\n            # 1) Clear Tetris lines\\n            lines = self.clear_lines()\\n            if lines > 0:\\n                line_base = TETRIS_SCORES.get(lines, lines * 200)\\n                gain = int(line_base * multiplier)\\n                self.score += gain\\n                total_gain += gain\\n\\n            # 2) Clear Bejeweled matches\\n            gems = self.clear_matches()\\n            if gems > 0:\\n                match_base = gems * 10\\n                gain = int(match_base * multiplier)\\n                self.score += gain\\n                total_gain += gain\\n\\n            # Stop if nothing cleared this chain level\\n            if lines == 0 and gems == 0:\\n                break\\n\\n        return total_gain\\n```\"}"}
