{"timestamp": "2026-05-22 12:46:48,560", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_gpt_conversation", "line": 403, "message": "{\n  \"event_type\": \"gpt_conversation\",\n  \"task_id\": \"task_6\",\n  \"conversation_type\": \"task_execution\",\n  \"iteration\": 1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"\\n# Role:\\nHelp me produce a precise and detailed solution for the given task. Follow these instructions exactly:\\n\\n# Objective & Steps:\\n1. Ensure Completeness:\\n   - Avoid placeholders or incomplete text.\\n   - Your output must meet all requirements of the task.\\n   - Include all necessary details so that the output is self-contained and can be directly used as input for downstream tasks.\\n\\n2. Maintain Precision and Clarity:\\n   - Your output will be used as input for subsequent tasks; therefore, it must be comprehensive and precise.\\n   - **Output the answer only without any jusifications**\\n\\n3. Avoid Repetition:\\n   - Do not repeat verbatim any content from previous tasks.\\n   - Ensure your output is original and adds value to the workflow.\\n\\n\\n\\n# Audience:\\nYour output will be used as a solution for the given task, it will be used in the later validation and intergration process.\\n\\n\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nDevelop a game that fuses Tetris and Bejeweled mechanics. \\nThis game needs to add keyboard control function.\\nFalling tetrominoes should lock into a grid and transform into colored gems. \\nThe game must support both Tetris line-clearing and Bejeweled match-3 clearing, triggering chain reactions and bonus points. \\nInclude a GUI (using a framework like Pygame) that displays the game grid, current score, and next tetromino preview, along with smooth animations. \\nNo sound effects are needed.\\n\\nOutput Format: python\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Implement clearing mechanics for Tetris line clears and Bejeweled match-3 clears, including chain reactions and bonus scoring.\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport random\\nfrom typing import List, Tuple, Optional\\n\\nfrom task0 import Grid, GemCell, Color\\n\\n\\n# Standard Tetris line clear scoring\\nTETRIS_SCORES = {\\n    1: 100,\\n    2: 300,\\n    3: 500,\\n    4: 800,\\n}\\n\\n\\nclass ClearingManager:\\n    def __init__(self, grid: Grid):\\n        self.grid = grid\\n        self.score = 0\\n\\n    def clear_lines(self) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Detects and removes all full rows, returns number of lines cleared.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        full_rows = [y for y in range(self.grid.height)\\n                     if all(self.grid.get_cell(x, y) is not None for x in range(self.grid.width))]\\n        if not full_rows:\\n            return 0\\n\\n        # Rebuild each column by filtering out cleared rows\\n        for x in range(self.grid.width):\\n            column_cells = [self.grid.get_cell(x, y) for y in range(self.grid.height)\\n                             if y not in full_rows]\\n            # Pad top with None\\n            new_col = [None] * len(full_rows) + column_cells\\n            for y, cell in enumerate(new_col):\\n                self.grid.set_cell(x, y, cell)\\n        return len(full_rows)\\n\\n    def find_matches(self) -> List[Tuple[int, int]]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Finds all match-3+ runs and returns unique gem coordinates.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        matches = set()\\n\\n        # Horizontal runs\\n        for y in range(self.grid.height):\\n            x = 0\\n            while x < self.grid.width - 2:\\n                cell = self.grid.get_cell(x, y)\\n                if cell is None:\\n                    x += 1\\n                    continue\\n                run_color = cell.color\\n                run_length = 1\\n                while x + run_length < self.grid.width and \\\\\\n                      self.grid.get_cell(x + run_length, y) and \\\\\\n                      self.grid.get_cell(x + run_length, y).color == run_color:\\n                    run_length += 1\\n                if run_length >= 3:\\n                    for rx in range(x, x + run_length):\\n                        matches.add((rx, y))\\n                x += run_length\\n        # Vertical runs\\n        for x in range(self.grid.width):\\n            y = 0\\n            while y < self.grid.height - 2:\\n                cell = self.grid.get_cell(x, y)\\n                if cell is None:\\n                    y += 1\\n                    continue\\n                run_color = cell.color\\n                run_length = 1\\n                while y + run_length < self.grid.height and \\\\\\n                      self.grid.get_cell(x, y + run_length) and \\\\\\n                      self.grid.get_cell(x, y + run_length).color == run_color:\\n                    run_length += 1\\n                if run_length >= 3:\\n                    for ry in range(y, y + run_length):\\n                        matches.add((x, ry))\\n                y += run_length\\n        return list(matches)\\n\\n    def clear_matches(self) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Clears all matched gems, drops floating gems, returns count cleared.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        matches = self.find_matches()\\n        if not matches:\\n            return 0\\n        for x, y in matches:\\n            self.grid.set_cell(x, y, None)\\n        self.drop_floating_gems()\\n        return len(matches)\\n\\n    def drop_floating_gems(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Gravity: drop gems down into empty spaces.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for x in range(self.grid.width):\\n            stack = [self.grid.get_cell(x, y) for y in range(self.grid.height)\\n                     if self.grid.get_cell(x, y) is not None]\\n            # pad with None at top\\n            new_col = [None] * (self.grid.height - len(stack)) + stack\\n            for y, cell in enumerate(new_col):\\n                self.grid.set_cell(x, y, cell)\\n\\n    def resolve_chains(self) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Repeatedly clears lines and matches until stable.\\n        Applies chain multipliers and returns total score gained.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        total_gain = 0\\n        chain_level = 0\\n\\n        while True:\\n            chain_level += 1\\n            multiplier = 1.0 + 0.5 * (chain_level - 1)\\n\\n            # 1) Clear Tetris lines\\n            lines = self.clear_lines()\\n            if lines > 0:\\n                line_base = TETRIS_SCORES.get(lines, lines * 200)\\n                gain = int(line_base * multiplier)\\n                self.score += gain\\n                total_gain += gain\\n\\n            # 2) Clear Bejeweled matches\\n            gems = self.clear_matches()\\n            if gems > 0:\\n                match_base = gems * 10\\n                gain = int(match_base * multiplier)\\n                self.score += gain\\n                total_gain += gain\\n\\n            # Stop if nothing cleared this chain level\\n            if lines == 0 and gems == 0:\\n                break\\n\\n        return total_gain\\n```\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Implement a 7-bag tetromino randomizer that shuffles all seven shapes per bag, maintain a next-piece preview queue of size 5, and expose methods to retrieve current and upcoming pieces.\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport random\\nfrom typing import List, Optional\\nfrom task0 import Tetromino, TETROMINO_SHAPES\\n\\nclass TetrominoGenerator:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    Implements a 7-bag tetromino randomizer with a preview queue.\\n\\n    Attributes:\\n        preview_size (int): Number of upcoming pieces to maintain.\\n        _bag (List[str]): Current bag of shape IDs to draw from.\\n        _queue (List[Tetromino]): Queue of next Tetromino instances.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\n    def __init__(self, preview_size: int = 5):\\n        self.preview_size: int = preview_size\\n        self._bag: List[str] = []\\n        self._queue: List[Tetromino] = []\\n        self._fill_bag()\\n        self._fill_queue()\\n\\n    def _fill_bag(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Refill and shuffle the 7-bag of tetromino shape IDs.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self._bag = list(TETROMINO_SHAPES.keys())\\n        random.shuffle(self._bag)\\n\\n    def _generate_tetromino(self) -> Tetromino:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Pop one shape ID from the bag, refill if empty,\\n        and return a new Tetromino instance.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not self._bag:\\n            self._fill_bag()\\n        shape_id = self._bag.pop()\\n        return Tetromino(shape_id=shape_id, rotations=TETROMINO_SHAPES[shape_id].rotations, color=TETROMINO_SHAPES[shape_id].color)\\n\\n    def _fill_queue(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Populate the preview queue up to preview_size.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        while len(self._queue) < self.preview_size:\\n            self._queue.append(self._generate_tetromino())\\n\\n    def get_next_tetromino(self) -> Tetromino:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Retrieve and remove the next tetromino from the queue,\\n        then enqueue a new random tetromino from the bag.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if not self._queue:\\n            # Should never happen, but safeguard\\n            self._fill_queue()\\n        next_piece = self._queue.pop(0)\\n        self._queue.append(self._generate_tetromino())\\n        return next_piece\\n\\n    def peek_next_tetromino(self, index: int = 0) -> Optional[Tetromino]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Return the tetromino at position `index` in the preview queue\\n        without removing it. Returns None if index is out of range.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if 0 <= index < len(self._queue):\\n            return self._queue[index]\\n        return None\\n\\n    def get_preview_queue(self) -> List[Tetromino]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Return a copy of the full preview queue for display purposes.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return list(self._queue)\\n```\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Implement keyboard input handling for controlling tetromino movement, rotation, and dropping.\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport pygame\\n\\nfrom task0 import Color, GemCell, Tetromino, TETROMINO_SHAPES, Grid\\nfrom task1 import TetrominoManager\\n\\n\\nclass TetrisBejeweled:\\n    def __init__(self, width: int, height: int, cell_size: int = 30):\\n        pygame.init()\\n        self.width = width\\n        self.height = height\\n        self.cell_size = cell_size\\n        self.grid = Grid(width, height)\\n        self.tetromino_manager = TetrominoManager(self.grid)\\n        self.screen = pygame.display.set_mode((width * cell_size, height * cell_size))\\n        pygame.display.set_caption(\\\"Tetris Bejeweled\\\")\\n        self.clock = pygame.time.Clock()\\n        self.score = 0\\n        self.game_over = False\\n        self.drop_timer = 0\\n        self.drop_speed = 500  # Milliseconds\\n\\n    def handle_input(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Handles keyboard input for controlling the tetromino.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for event in pygame.event.get():\\n            if event.type == pygame.QUIT:\\n                self.game_over = True\\n            if event.type == pygame.KEYDOWN:\\n                if event.key == pygame.K_LEFT:\\n                    self.tetromino_manager.move(-1)\\n                if event.key == pygame.K_RIGHT:\\n                    self.tetromino_manager.move(1)\\n                if event.key == pygame.K_UP:\\n                    self.tetromino_manager.rotate()\\n                if event.key == pygame.K_DOWN:\\n                    self.drop_speed = 50 # increase drop speed\\n                if event.key == pygame.K_SPACE:\\n                    while not self.tetromino_manager.move_down():  # Hard drop\\n                        pass\\n        keys = pygame.key.get_pressed()\\n        if not keys[pygame.K_DOWN]:\\n            self.drop_speed = 500 # reset drop speed\\n\\n    def update(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Updates the game state.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if self.tetromino_manager.current_tetromino is None:\\n            self.game_over = True\\n            return\\n\\n        self.drop_timer += self.clock.get_rawtime()\\n        self.clock.tick()\\n\\n        if self.drop_timer > self.drop_speed:\\n            self.drop_timer = 0\\n            if self.tetromino_manager.move_down():\\n                self.clear_lines()\\n                self.clear_matches()\\n\\n    def clear_lines(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Clears full lines in the grid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        lines_to_clear = []\\n        for y in range(self.height):\\n            if all(self.grid.get_cell(x, y) is not None for x in range(self.width)):\\n                lines_to_clear.append(y)\\n\\n        for line in lines_to_clear:\\n            self.grid.clear_line(line)\\n            self.score += 100  # Award points for clearing lines\\n\\n    def clear_matches(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Clears gem matches in the grid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        matches = self.find_matches()\\n        if matches:\\n            self.remove_matches(matches)\\n            self.score += len(matches) * 50  # Award points for clearing matches\\n            self.drop_gems()\\n            self.clear_matches()  # Chain reaction\\n\\n    def find_matches(self) -> list[list[tuple[int, int]]]:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Finds gem matches (3 or more in a row) in the grid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        matches: list[list[tuple[int, int]]] = []\\n\\n        # Horizontal matches\\n        for y in range(self.height):\\n            for x in range(self.width - 2):\\n                gem1 = self.grid.get_cell(x, y)\\n                gem2 = self.grid.get_cell(x + 1, y)\\n                gem3 = self.grid.get_cell(x + 2, y)\\n                if gem1 and gem2 and gem3 and gem1.color == gem2.color == gem3.color:\\n                    match = [(x, y), (x + 1, y), (x + 2, y)]\\n                    x_temp = x + 3\\n                    while x_temp < self.width and self.grid.get_cell(x_temp, y) and self.grid.get_cell(x_temp, y).color == gem1.color:\\n                        match.append((x_temp, y))\\n                        x_temp += 1\\n                    matches.append(match)\\n\\n        # Vertical matches\\n        for x in range(self.width):\\n            for y in range(self.height - 2):\\n                gem1 = self.grid.get_cell(x, y)\\n                gem2 = self.grid.get_cell(x, y + 1)\\n                gem3 = self.grid.get_cell(x, y + 2)\\n                if gem1 and gem2 and gem3 and gem1.color == gem2.color == gem3.color:\\n                    match = [(x, y), (x, y + 1), (x, y + 2)]\\n                    y_temp = y + 3\\n                    while y_temp < self.height and self.grid.get_cell(x, y_temp) and self.grid.get_cell(x, y_temp).color == gem1.color:\\n                        match.append((x, y_temp))\\n                        y_temp += 1\\n                    matches.append(match)\\n        \\n        # Remove duplicate matches\\n        unique_matches: list[list[tuple[int, int]]] = []\\n        for match in matches:\\n            if match not in unique_matches:\\n                unique_matches.append(match)\\n        return unique_matches\\n\\n    def remove_matches(self, matches: list[list[tuple[int, int]]]) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Removes matched gems from the grid.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for match in matches:\\n            for x, y in match:\\n                self.grid.set_cell(x, y, None)\\n\\n    def drop_gems(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Drops gems down to fill empty spaces.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for x in range(self.width):\\n            empty_space = -1\\n            for y in range(self.height - 1, -1, -1):\\n                if self.grid.get_cell(x,y) is None:\\n                    empty_space = y\\n                    break\\n            if empty_space == -1:\\n                continue\\n\\n            for y in range(empty_space - 1, -1, -1):\\n                if self.grid.get_cell(x,y) is not None:\\n                    self.grid.set_cell(x, empty_space, self.grid.get_cell(x,y))\\n                    self.grid.set_cell(x, y, None)\\n                    empty_space -= 1\\n\\n    def draw(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Draws the game grid, tetromino, and score on the screen.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.screen.fill((0, 0, 0))  # Black background\\n\\n        # Draw the grid\\n        for x in range(self.width):\\n            for y in range(self.height):\\n                cell = self.grid.get_cell(x, y)\\n                if cell:\\n                    pygame.draw.rect(\\n                        self.screen,\\n                        cell.color.value,\\n                        (x * self.cell_size, y * self.cell_size, self.cell_size, self.cell_size),\\n                    )\\n                    pygame.draw.rect(\\n                        self.screen,\\n                        (50, 50, 50),\\n                        (x * self.cell_size, y * self.cell_size, self.cell_size, self.cell_size),\\n                        1,\\n                    )\\n\\n        # Draw the current tetromino\\n        tetromino_cells = self.tetromino_manager.get_tetromino_cells()\\n        if tetromino_cells:\\n            for x, y, color in tetromino_cells:\\n                pygame.draw.rect(\\n                    self.screen,\\n                    color.value,\\n                    (x * self.cell_size, y * self.cell_size, self.cell_size, self.cell_size),\\n                )\\n                pygame.draw.rect(\\n                    self.screen,\\n                    (50, 50, 50),\\n                    (x * self.cell_size, y * self.cell_size, self.cell_size, self.cell_size),\\n                    1,\\n                )\\n\\n        # Display the score\\n        font = pygame.font.Font(None, 36)\\n        text = font.render(f\\\"Score: {self.score}\\\", True, (255, 255, 255))\\n        self.screen.blit(text, (10, 10))\\n\\n        pygame.display.flip()\\n\\n    def run(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Main game loop.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        while not self.game_over:\\n            self.handle_input()\\n            self.update()\\n            self.draw()\\n\\n        print(f\\\"Game Over! Final Score: {self.score}\\\")\\n        pygame.quit()\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    game = TetrisBejeweled(10, 20)\\n    game.run()\\n```\\nTask task5:\\n  Objective: Build GUI rendering module using Pygame: display game grid, current gems, active tetromino, next-piece preview, and score with animations.\\n  Result: ```python\\nimport pygame\\nfrom task0 import Grid, GemCell, Tetromino, Color\\nfrom task3 import TetrominoGenerator\\nfrom typing import List, Tuple, Optional\\n\\nclass GUIRenderer:\\n    def __init__(\\n        self,\\n        grid: Grid,\\n        tetromino_generator: TetrominoGenerator,\\n        cell_size: int = 30,\\n        grid_x_offset: int = 50,\\n        grid_y_offset: int = 50,\\n        preview_x_offset: int = 350,\\n        preview_y_offset: int = 50\\n    ):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Initializes the GUI renderer.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            grid: The game grid.\\n            tetromino_generator: The tetromino generator.\\n            cell_size: Size of each cell in pixels.\\n            grid_x_offset: X offset of grid.\\n            grid_y_offset: Y offset of grid.\\n            preview_x_offset: X offset of next-piece preview.\\n            preview_y_offset: Y offset of next-piece preview.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.grid = grid\\n        self.tetromino_generator = tetromino_generator\\n        self.cell_size = cell_size\\n        self.grid_x_offset = grid_x_offset\\n        self.grid_y_offset = grid_y_offset\\n        self.preview_x_offset = preview_x_offset\\n        self.preview_y_offset = preview_y_offset\\n\\n        self.screen: Optional[pygame.Surface] = None\\n        self.font: Optional[pygame.font.Font] = None\\n\\n    def initialize_screen(self, width: int, height: int):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Initializes the Pygame screen and font.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        pygame.init()\\n        self.screen = pygame.display.set_mode((width, height))\\n        pygame.display.set_caption(\\\"Tetris Bejeweled\\\")\\n        self.font = pygame.font.Font(None, 36)\\n\\n    def draw_grid(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Draws the game grid and its colored gems.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for y in range(self.grid.height):\\n            for x in range(self.grid.width):\\n                cell = self.grid.get_cell(x, y)\\n                rect = pygame.Rect(\\n                    self.grid_x_offset + x * self.cell_size,\\n                    self.grid_y_offset + y * self.cell_size,\\n                    self.cell_size,\\n                    self.cell_size\\n                )\\n                if cell:\\n                    # Draw filled gem\\n                    pygame.draw.rect(self.screen, cell.color.value, rect)\\n                    pygame.draw.rect(self.screen, (50, 50, 50), rect, 1)\\n                else:\\n                    # Empty cell border\\n                    pygame.draw.rect(self.screen, (128, 128, 128), rect, 1)\\n\\n    def draw_tetromino(self, tetromino: Tetromino, rotation_index: int, x_grid: int, y_grid: int):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Draws the active tetromino at grid position (x_grid, y_grid).\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        shape = tetromino.rotations[rotation_index]\\n        for dx, dy in shape:\\n            gx, gy = x_grid + dx, y_grid + dy\\n            if self.grid.is_inside(gx, gy):\\n                rect = pygame.Rect(\\n                    self.grid_x_offset + gx * self.cell_size,\\n                    self.grid_y_offset + gy * self.cell_size,\\n                    self.cell_size,\\n                    self.cell_size\\n                )\\n                pygame.draw.rect(self.screen, tetromino.color.value, rect)\\n                pygame.draw.rect(self.screen, (50, 50, 50), rect, 1)\\n\\n    def draw_next_piece_preview(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Draws the upcoming tetromino preview queue.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        preview_queue = self.tetromino_generator.get_preview_queue()\\n        for i, tetromino in enumerate(preview_queue):\\n            shape = tetromino.rotations[0]  # fixed orientation for preview\\n            base_x = self.preview_x_offset\\n            base_y = self.preview_y_offset + i * 3 * self.cell_size\\n            for dx, dy in shape:\\n                rect = pygame.Rect(\\n                    base_x + dx * self.cell_size,\\n                    base_y + dy * self.cell_size,\\n                    self.cell_size,\\n                    self.cell_size\\n                )\\n                pygame.draw.rect(self.screen, tetromino.color.value, rect)\\n                pygame.draw.rect(self.screen, (50, 50, 50), rect, 1)\\n\\n    def draw_score(self, score: int):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Renders the current score.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        text = f\\\"Score: {score}\\\"\\n        text_surf = self.font.render(text, True, (255, 255, 255))\\n        self.screen.blit(text_surf, (self.preview_x_offset, self.preview_y_offset + 4 * self.cell_size))\\n\\n    def render(\\n        self,\\n        active_tetromino: Tetromino,\\n        active_x: int,\\n        active_y: int,\\n        active_rotation: int,\\n        score: int\\n    ):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Full-screen render: grid, active piece, preview, and score.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        self.screen.fill((0, 0, 0))\\n        self.draw_grid()\\n        self.draw_tetromino(active_tetromino, active_rotation, active_x, active_y)\\n        self.draw_next_piece_preview()\\n        self.draw_score(score)\\n        pygame.display.flip()\\n\\n    def handle_animations(\\n        self,\\n        clear_lines: List[int],\\n        matched_cells: Optional[List[Tuple[int, int]]] = None\\n    ):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        Animates both line clears and gem matches with a simple flash.\\n\\n        Args:\\n            clear_lines: Row indices that were cleared (Tetris).\\n            matched_cells: List of (x, y) gem positions cleared by match-3.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        matched_cells = matched_cells or []\\n        flash_color = (255, 255, 255)\\n        for _ in range(3):  # flash 3 times\\n            self.screen.fill((0, 0, 0))\\n            self.draw_grid()\\n            # Line-clear flash\\n            for row in clear_lines:\\n                for x in range(self.grid.width):\\n                    rect = pygame.Rect(\\n                        self.grid_x_offset + x * self.cell_size,\\n                        self.grid_y_offset + row * self.cell_size,\\n                        self.cell_size,\\n                        self.cell_size\\n                    )\\n                    pygame.draw.rect(self.screen, flash_color, rect)\\n            # Gem-match flash\\n            for gx, gy in matched_cells:\\n                rect = pygame.Rect(\\n                    self.grid_x_offset + gx * self.cell_size,\\n                    self.grid_y_offset + gy * self.cell_size,\\n                    self.cell_size,\\n                    self.cell_size\\n                )\\n                pygame.draw.rect(self.screen, flash_color, rect)\\n            pygame.display.flip()\\n            pygame.time.delay(100)\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nNo downstream objectives available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nIntegrate core mechanics, input handling, generator, clearing logic, and GUI into the main game loop.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPython code\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\nimport pygame\\nimport random\\nfrom typing import List, Tuple, Optional\\n\\nfrom task0 import Grid, GemCell, Color, Tetromino, TETROMINO_SHAPES\\nfrom task1 import TetrominoManager\\nfrom task2 import ClearingManager\\nfrom task3 import TetrominoGenerator\\nfrom task4 import TetrisBejeweled\\nfrom task5 import GUIRenderer\\n\\n\\nclass TetrisBejeweledGame:\\n    def __init__(self, width: int = 10, height: int = 20, cell_size: int = 30):\\n        self.width = width\\n        self.height = height\\n        self.cell_size = cell_size\\n        self.grid = Grid(width, height)\\n        self.tetromino_generator = TetrominoGenerator(preview_size=5)\\n        self.tetromino_manager = TetrominoManager(self.grid, self.tetromino_generator)\\n        self.clearing_manager = ClearingManager(self.grid)\\n        self.gui_renderer = GUIRenderer(self.grid, self.tetromino_generator, cell_size=cell_size)\\n\\n        self.screen_width = 600\\n        self.screen_height = height * cell_size + 100  # Add space for score\\n        self.gui_renderer.initialize_screen(self.screen_width, self.screen_height)\\n\\n        self.clock = pygame.time.Clock()\\n        self.score = 0\\n        self.game_over = False\\n        self.drop_timer = 0\\n        self.drop_speed = 500  # Milliseconds\\n\\n        self.active_tetromino: Optional[Tetromino] = None\\n        self.active_x: int = 0\\n        self.active_y: int = 0\\n        self.active_rotation: int = 0\\n        self.new_tetromino()\\n\\n    def new_tetromino(self):\\n        self.active_tetromino = self.tetromino_generator.get_next_tetromino()\\n        self.active_x = self.width // 2 - 2\\n        self.active_y = 0\\n        self.active_rotation = 0\\n\\n        if not self.is_valid_position(self.active_tetromino.rotations[self.active_rotation], self.active_x, self.active_y):\\n            self.game_over = True\\n\\n    def is_valid_position(self, shape: List[Tuple[int, int]], x: int, y: int) -> bool:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Check if the given tetromino shape can be placed at the given position.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for dx, dy in shape:\\n            gx, gy = x + dx, y + dy\\n            if not (0 <= gx < self.width and 0 <= gy < self.height and self.grid.get_cell(gx, gy) is None):\\n                return False\\n        return True\\n\\n    def lock_tetromino(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Lock the active tetromino into the grid as gems.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if self.active_tetromino is None:\\n            return\\n\\n        shape = self.active_tetromino.rotations[self.active_rotation]\\n        for dx, dy in shape:\\n            x, y = self.active_x + dx, self.active_y + dy\\n            if 0 <= x < self.width and 0 <= y < self.height:\\n                self.grid.set_cell(x, y, GemCell(self.active_tetromino.color))\\n\\n        self.active_tetromino = None  # Tetromino is no longer active\\n        lines_cleared = self.clearing_manager.clear_lines()\\n        if lines_cleared > 0:\\n            self.score += lines_cleared * 100\\n        \\n        total_gain = self.clearing_manager.resolve_chains()\\n        self.score += total_gain\\n        self.new_tetromino()\\n\\n    def handle_input(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Handles keyboard input for controlling the tetromino.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        for event in pygame.event.get():\\n            if event.type == pygame.QUIT:\\n                self.game_over = True\\n            if event.type == pygame.KEYDOWN:\\n                if event.key == pygame.K_LEFT:\\n                    self.move(-1)\\n                if event.key == pygame.K_RIGHT:\\n                    self.move(1)\\n                if event.key == pygame.K_UP:\\n                    self.rotate()\\n                if event.key == pygame.K_DOWN:\\n                    self.drop_speed = 50 # increase drop speed\\n                if event.key == pygame.K_SPACE:\\n                    while not self.move_down():  # Hard drop\\n                        pass\\n        keys = pygame.key.get_pressed()\\n        if not keys[pygame.K_DOWN]:\\n            self.drop_speed = 500 # reset drop speed\\n    \\n    def move(self, dx: int):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Moves the active tetromino horizontally.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if self.active_tetromino is None:\\n            return\\n        new_x = self.active_x + dx\\n        if self.is_valid_position(self.active_tetromino.rotations[self.active_rotation], new_x, self.active_y):\\n            self.active_x = new_x\\n\\n    def rotate(self):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Rotates the active tetromino.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if self.active_tetromino is None:\\n            return\\n        new_rotation = (self.active_rotation + 1) % len(self.active_tetromino.rotations)\\n        if self.is_valid_position(self.active_tetromino.rotations[new_rotation], self.active_x, self.active_y):\\n            self.active_rotation = new_rotation\\n\\n    def move_down(self) -> bool:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Moves the active tetromino down by one cell.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if self.active_tetromino is None:\\n            return True\\n\\n        new_y = self.active_y + 1\\n        if self.is_valid_position(self.active_tetromino.rotations[self.active_rotation], self.active_x, new_y):\\n            self.active_y = new_y\\n            return False\\n        else:\\n            self.lock_tetromino()\\n            return True\\n\\n    def update(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Updates the game state.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if self.game_over:\\n            return\\n\\n        if self.active_tetromino is None:\\n            return\\n\\n        self.drop_timer += self.clock.get_rawtime()\\n        self.clock.tick()\\n\\n        if self.drop_timer > self.drop_speed:\\n            self.drop_timer = 0\\n            self.move_down()\\n    \\n    def draw(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Draws the game elements on the screen.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if self.gui_renderer.screen is None:\\n            raise ValueError(\\\"Screen not initialized. Call initialize_screen() first.\\\")\\n        \\n        self.gui_renderer.render(\\n            active_tetromino=self.active_tetromino,\\n            active_x=self.active_x,\\n            active_y=self.active_y,\\n            active_rotation=self.active_rotation,\\n            score=self.score\\n        )\\n    \\n    def run(self) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Main game loop.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        while not self.game_over:\\n            self.handle_input()\\n            self.update()\\n            self.draw()\\n            pygame.display.flip()\\n            self.clock.tick(60)\\n\\n        print(f\\\"Game Over! Final Score: {self.score}\\\")\\n        pygame.quit()\\n\\n\\nif __name__ == \\\"__main__\\\":\\n    game = TetrisBejeweledGame()\\n    game.run()\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-22T12:46:48.559885\"\n}"}
